How Do You Read College Basketball Odds?

Reading college basketball betting odds is similar to other betting odds, especially NBA odds since they are the same sport. The NCAA basketball point spread favorite is always listed with a minus sign (-) and the underdog has their odds listed with a plus sign (+). Placing a point spread bet is a wager on the predicted spread determined top sportsbooks. When betting on the spread on the favorite, that team must win by the margin of points by which they are favored, whereas betting on the underdog means they cannot lose by that same point spread. For example, if the Gonzaga Bulldogs are favored by 3.5 points over the UCLA Bruins, then Gonzaga must win by at least 4 points to win the wager, otherwise UCLA would win the spread bet. There are occasions when the college basketball odds line is a whole number, in which case, the bet is a push and your money is returned if the margin of victory is exactly that point total.

Odds to Win the Wooden Award in College Basketball


The John R. Wooden Award is a prestigious achievement in college basketball, presented annually to the nation's most outstanding collegiate player. As such, Wooden Award odds attract substantial interest in the sports betting world. Place your bets on the latest odds to win the 2023-2024 Wooden Award with FanDuel Sportsbook. Will Duke claim their seventh Wooden Award? Or will another school in North Carolina win adding that total to 12 for the state? With FanDuel Sportsbook, you can wager on who will be the next Wooden Award winner throughout the entire year up until the award is announced on March 10, 2024.


Who Has the Best Odds to Win the Wooden Award?

Center Zach Edey from Purdue is the favorite to win the Wooden Award with -210 odds as we enter the 2023 regular season.. Other players with top odds to win the Wooden are both Kyle Filipowski and Hunter Dickinson with +550 odds, Donovan Clingan with +1300 odds. Additionally, Armando Bacot has +1700 odds, followed by Isaiah Collier with +3700 odds. These odds will update as the season progresses, so be sure to check back frequently to track odds changes

Understanding Wooden Award Odds

The Wooden Award odds in the table above indicates each player's likelihood of winning the award. These odds work similar to standard moneyline odds seen in other College Basketball Odds. For instance, if a player has odds of +800, a successful $100 bet on that player would yield $800 in winnings. You can also add a pick to a betslip and enter a bet amount to get the payout calculated without submitting a bet. These odds are dynamic and can change throughout the season based on player performances, injuries, and team success.

Factors Influencing Wooden Award Odds

Several factors influence the Wooden Award odds. To be eligible for the John R. Wooden Award in college basketball, nominees are required to be enrolled as full-time students and maintain a cumulative GPA of at least 2.00 during their college tenure. Additionally, these candidates should have demonstrated exceptional skill and contribution in both offensive and defensive play within their teams. Beyond their athletic prowess, they are also expected to exemplify commendable character and conduct, upholding high standards in their personal and public lives.
